# Platform scope

Harness has two clients: the **desktop app** (Electron) and **Harness Mobile** (iOS). Unless the user clearly asks for iOS work, agents should stay on desktop.

## Default: desktop only

Treat these as in scope without asking:

- `src/main/`, `src/preload/`, `src/renderer/`, `src/shared/`
- Root npm scripts, Electron build/config, Playwright e2e, desktop docs
- Shared TypeScript logic that backs desktop behavior (sync, themes, chat, tasks, etc.)

When a task is ambiguous (“fix sync”, “update chat UI”, “add a setting”), implement it for desktop first.

## iOS requires explicit scope

Do **not** edit `ios/` unless one of these is true:

1. The user explicitly asks for iOS / mobile / Swift / Harness Mobile work, or
2. You ask first and the user confirms iOS changes are wanted.

If a fix might belong on both platforms, ship the desktop change, then ask whether to mirror it on iOS.

## When both platforms are mentioned

If the user says “both”, “desktop and iOS”, or “everywhere”, work on both.

If they only say “the app” or “Harness” with no platform, assume **desktop**.

## Examples

| User request | Action |
|---|---|
| “Fix chat composer padding” | Desktop only (`src/renderer/`) |
| “Update sync merge logic” | Desktop first (`src/shared/`, `src/main/`); ask before `ios/` |
| “Add this to iOS too” | Desktop + iOS |
| “Fix the iPhone sync bug” | iOS (`ios/`) |
| “Make themes simpler” | Desktop only unless user names iOS |

## Out of scope unless asked

- Regenerating Xcode projects (`xcodegen`) or editing `ios/project.yml`
- SwiftUI views, Swift tests, or iOS-specific settings flows
- iOS README or simulator/device testing instructions
